Clang 21's NVPTX target already knows PTX 8.8 and the Blackwell SM variants,
but the Clang builtin availability table stops at PTX 8.7.  CUDA 13 JAX builds
pass --cuda-feature=+ptx88, which makes ordinary builtins such as
__nvvm_shfl_sync_idx_i32 appear unavailable because their "since PTX 6.0"
feature list does not include ptx88.

Make PTX 8.8 the newest Clang builtin feature so every lower minimum PTX level
continues to include PTX 8.8.

diff --git a/clang/include/clang/Basic/BuiltinsNVPTX.td b/clang/include/clang/Basic/BuiltinsNVPTX.td
index d4e4937b9c5b..90c8f1743512 100644
--- a/clang/include/clang/Basic/BuiltinsNVPTX.td
+++ b/clang/include/clang/Basic/BuiltinsNVPTX.td
@@ -50,7 +50,8 @@ class PTX<string version, PTXFeatures newer> : PTXFeatures {
   let Features = !strconcat("ptx", version, "|", newer.Features);
 }
 
-let Features = "ptx87" in def PTX87 : PTXFeatures;
+let Features = "ptx88" in def PTX88 : PTXFeatures;
+def PTX87 : PTX<"87", PTX88>;
 
 def PTX86 : PTX<"86", PTX87>;
 def PTX85 : PTX<"85", PTX86>;
